'''Arkansas State Hospital''', originally known as Arkansas Lunatic Asylum,<ref name=kb>{{cite web|url=http://www.kirkbridebuildings.com/buildings/little-rock/|work=Kirkbride Buildings|title=Arkansas State Hospital|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref> is the sole public [[psychiatric hospital]] in the state of [[Arkansas]], and is located in the city of [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock]]. It was established in 1883 and, as of 2017, is still active, though only with a focus on acute care rather than chronic. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://humanservices.arkansas.gov/dbhs/pages/arstatehospital.aspx|work=Department of Human Services: Arkansas|title=Arkansas State Hospital|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref> The building was constructed in the [[Kirkbride Plan|Kirkbride]] design. The original Kirkbride building was demolished in the 1960s.<ref name=kb/>
